title: Bass Traps / Acoustic Panels
post:
I'm downsizing my studio and as such selling a portion of my custom acoustic panels

-low VOC materials - Knaupf Earthwool, zero VOC pine plywood and glue
-covered in the thinnest possible painters plastic to keep insulation fibers from escaping and floating free. does not affect treble frequencies with the fabric over it.
-breathable black fabric outer wrap, front and back
-Pro aesthetic - beveled edges on the front of the wood frame, and a useful back frame that makes hanging options a breeze

I have:
4ft X 2ft X 4" Knaupf Earthwool $80 ea
4ft X 2ft X 2" Knaupf Earthwool $60 ea
4ft X 1ft X 4" Ultratouch Denim $60 ea

Custom made from extremely high quality materials that were selected for maximum acoustic effectiveness. As someone with asthma, acoustic panels can wreak havoc on your breathing and lung health (even if you don't have asthma) if not crafted/covered correctly -- so these are about the healthiest possible thing, half the price and a step up from mixmasteredacoustics, acoustical solutions, etc.

First come first serve. Let me know what quantity and size of panel you're interested in -- I have almost sold out of the 2" panels, prob 4 left.
